This paper deals with the classification of heart sounds using machine learning techniques, which falls under the domain of signal processing and pattern recognition. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also uses deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised learning techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.SI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses Support Vector Machines and Linear Discriminant Analysis, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with clinical data and uses classifiers, which are commonly used in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
